div.div:
evaluateAnswer method of each subclass has to take the string and depending on the type do specific stuff for example:
multiplechoice question -> take string -> split at "," -> iterate over rightAnswers array and check if values at i are equal to the values of the array we got with .split at the same index (parseInt has to be used since user enters strings)
(this forces the user to enter the answers he thinks are correct in an "ascending" way
e.g. 5 possible answers -> user thinks answer 2 and 4 are correct so his input has to be "2,4" and NOT "4,2" )
